The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Asia captaincy may be split

 - Jayawardene could lead in the Twenty20 International and Dravid in the three ODIs 

LOKENDRA PRATAP SAHI

 Mahela Jayawardene and Rahul Dravid 

Dhaka: Assuming both Rahul Dravid and Mahela

 Jayawardene are available, the Asia captaincy could be split for next months

 Afro-Asian Cup. 

According to The Telegraphs sources, Sri Lankas Jayawardene could lead in the one-off Twenty20 International against Africa, with Dravid getting the captaincy for the three ODIs in the Cup proper. 

The selectors meet here on Friday morning. 

Were awaiting confirmation of their availability... There could be two captains, one of the sources pointed out late on Thursday. 

Former India allrounder Roger Binny, one learns, could be the Asia coach. 

Bangalore hosts the Twenty20 International and the first ODI, on June 5 and 6, respectively. Chennai will stage the last two matches. 

The Cups inaugural edition had been hosted by South Africa in August 2005. 




